(354, 'Chương trình đào tạo Chuyên ngành Công nghệ kỹ thuật xây dựng Cầu đường sắt', '', 'Chương trình đào tạo Chuyên ngành Công nghệ kỹ thuật xây dựng Cầu đường sắt', '<p><strong>1. Mục ti&ecirc;u đ&agrave;o tạo chung của chuy&ecirc;n ng&agrave;nh</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chương tr&igrave;nh đ&agrave;o tạo Đại học Ch&iacute;nh quy C&ocirc;ng nghệ kỹ thuật x&acirc;y dựng cầu đường sắt nhằm trang bị cho người học sau khi tốt nghiệp c&oacute; kiến thức khoa học cơ bản, cơ sở, kỹ thuật chuy&ecirc;n m&ocirc;n to&agrave;n diện, năng lực thực h&agrave;nh nghề nghiệp cơ bản, năng lực tư duy s&aacute;ng tạo, khả năng th&iacute;ch ứng nhanh với những biến đổi trong lĩnh vực c&ocirc;ng nghệ x&acirc;y dựng cầu đường sắt; c&oacute; đạo đức nghề nghiệp, c&oacute; sức khỏe đ&aacute;p ứng y&ecirc;u cầu x&acirc;y dựng v&agrave; bảo vệ Tổ quốc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. C&aacute;c c&ocirc;ng vi&ecirc;̣c sinh vi&ecirc;n phụ tr&aacute;ch sau t&ocirc;́t nghi&ecirc;̣p</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>C&aacute;c kỹ sư Cầu đường sắt c&oacute; thể đảm nhiệm c&aacute;c c&ocirc;ng việc nghi&ecirc;n cứu, thiết kế, tư vấn gi&aacute;m &nbsp;s&aacute;t, quản l&yacute; dự &aacute;n, thi c&ocirc;ng x&acirc;y dựng c&aacute;c c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh Cầu, Đường sắt, Đường bộ;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Nơi l&agrave;m việc:</strong></em>&nbsp;L&agrave;m việc tại c&aacute;c cơ quan đ&agrave;o tạo - nghi&ecirc;n cứu khoa học, c&aacute;c cơ quan quản l&yacute; nh&agrave; nước, c&aacute;c đơn vị tư vấn thiết kế (kể cả c&aacute;c C&ocirc;ng ty nước ngo&agrave;i); c&aacute;c doanh nghiệp x&acirc;y dựng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh giao th&ocirc;ng, c&aacute;c Sở Giao th&ocirc;ng c&ocirc;ng ch&iacute;nh v&agrave; c&aacute;c ng&agrave;nh kinh tế kh&aacute;c.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>C&aacute;c c&ocirc;ng việc sinh vi&ecirc;n c&oacute; thể thực hiện sau khi ra trường:</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ Tổ chức c&ocirc;ng t&aacute;c đo đạc khảo s&aacute;t thu thập số liệu cần thiết cho thiết kế c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh cầu đường sắt;<br />\r\n+ Thiết kế; thiết kế thi c&ocirc;ng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh cầu đường sắt;<br />\r\n+ Chỉ đạo tổ chức thi c&ocirc;ng x&acirc;y dựng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh: Đường giao th&ocirc;ng, hệ thống tho&aacute;t nước, hạ tầng kỹ thuật c&aacute;c khu đ&ocirc; thị&hellip;<br />\r\n+ Kiểm tra v&agrave; nghiệm thu chất lượng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh cầu đường sắt;<br />\r\n+ Lập, tổ chức thực hiện, quản l&yacute; c&aacute;c dự &aacute;n đầu tư x&acirc;y dựng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh cầu đường sắt;<br />\r\n+ Quản l&yacute; khai th&aacute;c, kiểm định chất lượng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh cầu đường sắt;<br />\r\n+ Sử dụng ngoại ngữ, c&ocirc;ng nghệ th&ocirc;ng tin.. để nghi&ecirc;n cứu, ứng dụng hiệu quả tiến khoa học - c&ocirc;ng nghệ trong lĩnh vực kỹ thuật x&acirc;y dựng &nbsp;cầu đường sắt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Chuyên ngành Công nghệ Kỹ thuật xây dựng Cầu đường sắt" src="http://utt.edu.vn/home/images/stories/chuong-trinh-dao-tao-chuyen-nganh-cong-nghe-ky-thuat-xay-dung-cau-duong-sat-01.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:auto; margin:0px auto; max-width:100%; vertical-align:middle; width:750px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>C&aacute;c dự &aacute;n Đường sắt lớn đ&atilde; v&agrave; đang khởi c&ocirc;ng:</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ C&aacute;c g&oacute;i dự &aacute;n cải tạo n&acirc;ng cấp cầu đường sắt ( tr&ecirc;n tất cả c&aacute;c tuyến đường sắt);<br />\r\n+ Đường sắt Cao tốc Bắc &ndash; Nam;<br />\r\n+ Tuyến Đường sắt: S&agrave;i G&ograve;n &ndash; Vũng T&agrave;u; S&agrave;i G&ograve;n &ndash; Lộc Ninh; S&agrave;i G&ograve;n &ndash; Cần thơ;&hellip;<br />\r\n+ C&aacute;c tuyến Đường sắt Đ&ocirc; thị tại Tp. Hồ Ch&iacute; Minh: Bến Th&agrave;nh &ndash; Suối Ti&ecirc;n, Bến Th&agrave;nh &ndash; Tham Lương, Bến Th&agrave;nh &ndash; T&acirc;n B&igrave;nh,&hellip;<br />\r\n+ C&aacute;c tuyến Đường sắt Đ&ocirc; thị tại H&agrave; Nội: C&aacute;t Linh &ndash; H&agrave; Đ&ocirc;ng, Nhổ - Ga H&agrave; Nội, Nam Thăng Long &ndash; T&acirc;y H&agrave; Nội,&hellip;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Quan điểm x&acirc;y dựng chương tr&igrave;nh học cho sinh vi&ecirc;n v&agrave; nội dung chương tr&igrave;nh học</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Quan điểm x&acirc;y dựng chương tr&igrave;nh học cho sinh vi&ecirc;n:&nbsp;</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ Cung cấp cho sinh vi&ecirc;n đầy đủ c&aacute;c kiến thức khoa học cơ bản, cơ sở ng&agrave;nh để gi&uacute;p sinh vi&ecirc;n tiếp thu hiệu quả những kiến thức chuy&ecirc;n m&ocirc;n của ng&agrave;nh học;<br />\r\n+ Tăng cường c&aacute;c học phần thực h&agrave;nh thực tập, gi&uacute;p sinh vi&ecirc;n tiếp cận với m&ocirc;i trường thực tiễn, r&uacute;t ngắn khoảng c&aacute;ch giữa nh&agrave; trường v&agrave; m&ocirc;i trường l&agrave;m việc sau khi ra trường;<br />\r\n+ Chương tr&igrave;nh đ&agrave;o tạo được cập nhật những kiến thức mới, c&aacute;c c&ocirc;ng nghệ ti&ecirc;n tiến của Việt Nam v&agrave; tr&ecirc;n thế giới;<br />\r\n+ Cung cấp cho sinh vi&ecirc;n những c&ocirc;ng cụ hỗ trợ học tập v&agrave; l&agrave;m việc như: c&aacute;c phần mềm chuy&ecirc;n dụng, ngoại ngữ, tin học;<br />\r\n+ R&egrave;n sinh vi&ecirc;n khả năng tư duy tự học, tự t&iacute;ch lũy bổ sung kiến thức, tư duy nghi&ecirc;n cứu khoa học để c&oacute; khả năng nghi&ecirc;n cứu chuy&ecirc;n s&acirc;u;<br />\r\n+ R&egrave;n cho sinh vi&ecirc;n c&aacute;c kỹ năng ph&acirc;n t&iacute;ch, đ&aacute;nh gi&aacute;, tổng hợp giải quyết những vấn đề trong lĩnh vực chuy&ecirc;n ng&agrave;nh; R&egrave;n luyện khả năng thuyết tr&igrave;nh, l&agrave;m việc hiệu quả theo nh&oacute;m;<br />\r\n+ Song song với học kiến thức chuy&ecirc;n ng&agrave;nh l&agrave; r&egrave;n luyện thể chất, th&aacute;i độ v&agrave; t&aacute;c phong l&agrave;m việc, th&aacute;i độ phục vụ, đạo đức nghề nghiệp&hellip; nhằm gi&uacute;p sinh vi&ecirc;n ph&aacute;t triển một c&aacute;ch to&agrave;n diện nhất.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>STT</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>KHỐI KIẾN THỨC</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>Bắt buộc</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>Tự chọn</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>Tổng</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>1</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p><strong>Khối kiến thức gi&aacute;o dục đại cương</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>43</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>4</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>47</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>2</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p><strong>Kiến thức gi&aacute;o dục chuy&ecirc;n nghiệp</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>115</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>10</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>125</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>2.1</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p>Kiến thức cơ sở ng&agrave;nh</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>43</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>4</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>47</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>2.2</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p>Kiến thức ng&agrave;nh</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>39</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>6</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>45</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>2.3</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p>Thực tập nghề nghiệp</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>21</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>21</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>2.4</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p>Thực tập tốt nghiệp</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>4</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>4</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>2.5</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p>Đồ &aacute;n tốt nghiệp</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>8</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>8</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p><strong>Tổng cộng</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>158</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>14</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>172</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Kế hoạch học trong 5 năm</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Nội dung chi tiết của kế hoạch&nbsp;đề nghị xem tại tệp đ&iacute;nh k&egrave;m./.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5. C&aacute;c sinh hoạt kh&aacute;c</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Trường c&oacute; c&aacute;c c&acirc;u lạc bộ v&agrave; cơ sở vật chất phục vụ cho c&aacute;c hoạt động văn-thể-mỹ v&agrave; c&aacute;c hoạt động kh&aacute;c:</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ Thể thao: b&oacute;ng đ&aacute;, b&oacute;ng chuyền, b&oacute;ng b&agrave;n. . . tổ chức h&agrave;ng năm;<br />\r\n+ Văn nghệ: Ca, m&uacute;a nhạc;<br />\r\n+ C&acirc;u lạc bộ học thuật kh&aacute;c: Tiếng anh&hellip;</p>\r\n</div>', 16, 'vn', 1, 8, 'news', 25, 1440334007, NULL, NULL, 1),
(355, 'Chương trình đào tạo Chuyên ngành Công nghệ kỹ thuật xây dựng Cầu đường sắt', '130560531_635411336804520000_HasThumb_Thumb.jpg', 'Chương trình đào tạo Chuyên ngành Công nghệ kỹ thuật xây dựng Cầu đường sắt', '<p><a href="http://utt.edu.vn/home/dao-tao/chuong-trinh-dao-tao" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(32, 95, 147); text-decoration: none; background-color: transparent;">Chương tr&igrave;nh đ&agrave;o tạo</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Được đăng:&nbsp;<strong>18.08.2015</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lượt xem: 317</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href="http://utt.edu.vn/home/dao-tao/chuong-trinh-dao-tao/1483-chuong-trinh-dao-tao-chuyen-nganh-cong-nghe-ky-thuat-xay-dung-cau-duong-sat?tmpl=component&amp;print=1&amp;layout=default&amp;page=" rel="nofollow" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(153, 153, 153); text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; font-size: 0px; text-indent: -999em; width: 14px; background-color: transparent;" title="In bài này">&nbsp;In b&agrave;i n&agrave;y&nbsp;</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://utt.edu.vn/home/component/mailto/?tmpl=component&amp;template=ja_university_t3&amp;link=ec33795f5d3617dbca536fd164515ab76406d7a6" style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(153, 153, 153); text-decoration: none; display: inline-block; font-size: 0px; text-indent: -999em; width: 14px; background-color: transparent;" title="Gửi Email bài này">&nbsp;Gửi Email b&agrave;i n&agrave;y</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1. Mục ti&ecirc;u đ&agrave;o tạo chung của chuy&ecirc;n ng&agrave;nh</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chương tr&igrave;nh đ&agrave;o tạo Đại học Ch&iacute;nh quy C&ocirc;ng nghệ kỹ thuật x&acirc;y dựng cầu đường sắt nhằm trang bị cho người học sau khi tốt nghiệp c&oacute; kiến thức khoa học cơ bản, cơ sở, kỹ thuật chuy&ecirc;n m&ocirc;n to&agrave;n diện, năng lực thực h&agrave;nh nghề nghiệp cơ bản, năng lực tư duy s&aacute;ng tạo, khả năng th&iacute;ch ứng nhanh với những biến đổi trong lĩnh vực c&ocirc;ng nghệ x&acirc;y dựng cầu đường sắt; c&oacute; đạo đức nghề nghiệp, c&oacute; sức khỏe đ&aacute;p ứng y&ecirc;u cầu x&acirc;y dựng v&agrave; bảo vệ Tổ quốc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>2. C&aacute;c c&ocirc;ng vi&ecirc;̣c sinh vi&ecirc;n phụ tr&aacute;ch sau t&ocirc;́t nghi&ecirc;̣p</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>C&aacute;c kỹ sư Cầu đường sắt c&oacute; thể đảm nhiệm c&aacute;c c&ocirc;ng việc nghi&ecirc;n cứu, thiết kế, tư vấn gi&aacute;m &nbsp;s&aacute;t, quản l&yacute; dự &aacute;n, thi c&ocirc;ng x&acirc;y dựng c&aacute;c c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh Cầu, Đường sắt, Đường bộ;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Nơi l&agrave;m việc:</strong></em>&nbsp;L&agrave;m việc tại c&aacute;c cơ quan đ&agrave;o tạo - nghi&ecirc;n cứu khoa học, c&aacute;c cơ quan quản l&yacute; nh&agrave; nước, c&aacute;c đơn vị tư vấn thiết kế (kể cả c&aacute;c C&ocirc;ng ty nước ngo&agrave;i); c&aacute;c doanh nghiệp x&acirc;y dựng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh giao th&ocirc;ng, c&aacute;c Sở Giao th&ocirc;ng c&ocirc;ng ch&iacute;nh v&agrave; c&aacute;c ng&agrave;nh kinh tế kh&aacute;c.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>C&aacute;c c&ocirc;ng việc sinh vi&ecirc;n c&oacute; thể thực hiện sau khi ra trường:</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ Tổ chức c&ocirc;ng t&aacute;c đo đạc khảo s&aacute;t thu thập số liệu cần thiết cho thiết kế c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh cầu đường sắt;<br />\r\n+ Thiết kế; thiết kế thi c&ocirc;ng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh cầu đường sắt;<br />\r\n+ Chỉ đạo tổ chức thi c&ocirc;ng x&acirc;y dựng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh: Đường giao th&ocirc;ng, hệ thống tho&aacute;t nước, hạ tầng kỹ thuật c&aacute;c khu đ&ocirc; thị&hellip;<br />\r\n+ Kiểm tra v&agrave; nghiệm thu chất lượng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh cầu đường sắt;<br />\r\n+ Lập, tổ chức thực hiện, quản l&yacute; c&aacute;c dự &aacute;n đầu tư x&acirc;y dựng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh cầu đường sắt;<br />\r\n+ Quản l&yacute; khai th&aacute;c, kiểm định chất lượng c&ocirc;ng tr&igrave;nh cầu đường sắt;<br />\r\n+ Sử dụng ngoại ngữ, c&ocirc;ng nghệ th&ocirc;ng tin.. để nghi&ecirc;n cứu, ứng dụng hiệu quả tiến khoa học - c&ocirc;ng nghệ trong lĩnh vực kỹ thuật x&acirc;y dựng &nbsp;cầu đường sắt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Chuyên ngành Công nghệ Kỹ thuật xây dựng Cầu đường sắt" src="http://utt.edu.vn/home/images/stories/chuong-trinh-dao-tao-chuyen-nganh-cong-nghe-ky-thuat-xay-dung-cau-duong-sat-01.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:auto; margin:0px auto; max-width:100%; vertical-align:middle; width:750px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>C&aacute;c dự &aacute;n Đường sắt lớn đ&atilde; v&agrave; đang khởi c&ocirc;ng:</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ C&aacute;c g&oacute;i dự &aacute;n cải tạo n&acirc;ng cấp cầu đường sắt ( tr&ecirc;n tất cả c&aacute;c tuyến đường sắt);<br />\r\n+ Đường sắt Cao tốc Bắc &ndash; Nam;<br />\r\n+ Tuyến Đường sắt: S&agrave;i G&ograve;n &ndash; Vũng T&agrave;u; S&agrave;i G&ograve;n &ndash; Lộc Ninh; S&agrave;i G&ograve;n &ndash; Cần thơ;&hellip;<br />\r\n+ C&aacute;c tuyến Đường sắt Đ&ocirc; thị tại Tp. Hồ Ch&iacute; Minh: Bến Th&agrave;nh &ndash; Suối Ti&ecirc;n, Bến Th&agrave;nh &ndash; Tham Lương, Bến Th&agrave;nh &ndash; T&acirc;n B&igrave;nh,&hellip;<br />\r\n+ C&aacute;c tuyến Đường sắt Đ&ocirc; thị tại H&agrave; Nội: C&aacute;t Linh &ndash; H&agrave; Đ&ocirc;ng, Nhổ - Ga H&agrave; Nội, Nam Thăng Long &ndash; T&acirc;y H&agrave; Nội,&hellip;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3. Quan điểm x&acirc;y dựng chương tr&igrave;nh học cho sinh vi&ecirc;n v&agrave; nội dung chương tr&igrave;nh học</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Quan điểm x&acirc;y dựng chương tr&igrave;nh học cho sinh vi&ecirc;n:&nbsp;</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ Cung cấp cho sinh vi&ecirc;n đầy đủ c&aacute;c kiến thức khoa học cơ bản, cơ sở ng&agrave;nh để gi&uacute;p sinh vi&ecirc;n tiếp thu hiệu quả những kiến thức chuy&ecirc;n m&ocirc;n của ng&agrave;nh học;<br />\r\n+ Tăng cường c&aacute;c học phần thực h&agrave;nh thực tập, gi&uacute;p sinh vi&ecirc;n tiếp cận với m&ocirc;i trường thực tiễn, r&uacute;t ngắn khoảng c&aacute;ch giữa nh&agrave; trường v&agrave; m&ocirc;i trường l&agrave;m việc sau khi ra trường;<br />\r\n+ Chương tr&igrave;nh đ&agrave;o tạo được cập nhật những kiến thức mới, c&aacute;c c&ocirc;ng nghệ ti&ecirc;n tiến của Việt Nam v&agrave; tr&ecirc;n thế giới;<br />\r\n+ Cung cấp cho sinh vi&ecirc;n những c&ocirc;ng cụ hỗ trợ học tập v&agrave; l&agrave;m việc như: c&aacute;c phần mềm chuy&ecirc;n dụng, ngoại ngữ, tin học;<br />\r\n+ R&egrave;n sinh vi&ecirc;n khả năng tư duy tự học, tự t&iacute;ch lũy bổ sung kiến thức, tư duy nghi&ecirc;n cứu khoa học để c&oacute; khả năng nghi&ecirc;n cứu chuy&ecirc;n s&acirc;u;<br />\r\n+ R&egrave;n cho sinh vi&ecirc;n c&aacute;c kỹ năng ph&acirc;n t&iacute;ch, đ&aacute;nh gi&aacute;, tổng hợp giải quyết những vấn đề trong lĩnh vực chuy&ecirc;n ng&agrave;nh; R&egrave;n luyện khả năng thuyết tr&igrave;nh, l&agrave;m việc hiệu quả theo nh&oacute;m;<br />\r\n+ Song song với học kiến thức chuy&ecirc;n ng&agrave;nh l&agrave; r&egrave;n luyện thể chất, th&aacute;i độ v&agrave; t&aacute;c phong l&agrave;m việc, th&aacute;i độ phục vụ, đạo đức nghề nghiệp&hellip; nhằm gi&uacute;p sinh vi&ecirc;n ph&aacute;t triển một c&aacute;ch to&agrave;n diện nhất.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<table>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>STT</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>KHỐI KIẾN THỨC</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>Bắt buộc</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>Tự chọn</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>Tổng</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>1</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p><strong>Khối kiến thức gi&aacute;o dục đại cương</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>43</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>4</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>47</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>2</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p><strong>Kiến thức gi&aacute;o dục chuy&ecirc;n nghiệp</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>115</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>10</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>125</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>2.1</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p>Kiến thức cơ sở ng&agrave;nh</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>43</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>4</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>47</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>2.2</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p>Kiến thức ng&agrave;nh</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>39</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>6</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>45</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>2.3</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p>Thực tập nghề nghiệp</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>21</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>21</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>2.4</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p>Thực tập tốt nghiệp</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>4</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>4</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>2.5</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p>Đồ &aacute;n tốt nghiệp</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>8</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>8</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style="border-color:rgb(221, 221, 221) windowtext windowtext; text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="height:21.95pt; vertical-align:middle; width:248pt">\r\n			<p><strong>Tổng cộng</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>158</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>14</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style="text-align:center; vertical-align:middle">\r\n			<p><strong>172</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4. Kế hoạch học trong 5 năm</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Nội dung chi tiết của kế hoạch&nbsp;đề nghị xem tại tệp đ&iacute;nh k&egrave;m./.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5. C&aacute;c sinh hoạt kh&aacute;c</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Trường c&oacute; c&aacute;c c&acirc;u lạc bộ v&agrave; cơ sở vật chất phục vụ cho c&aacute;c hoạt động văn-thể-mỹ v&agrave; c&aacute;c hoạt động kh&aacute;c:</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>+ Thể thao: b&oacute;ng đ&aacute;, b&oacute;ng chuyền, b&oacute;ng b&agrave;n. . . tổ chức h&agrave;ng năm;<br />\r\n+ Văn nghệ: Ca, m&uacute;a nhạc;<br />\r\n+ C&acirc;u lạc bộ học thuật kh&aacute;c: Tiếng anh&hellip;</p>\r\n</div>', 16, 'vn', 1, 8, 'news', 25, 1440334050, NULL, NULL, 1);
INSERT INTO `utt_post` (`id`, `title`, `image`, `description`, `detail`, `site_id`, `lang`, `status`, `user_id`, `post_type`, `cate_id`, `time_create`, `time_update`, `sort`, `is_top`) VALUES
(356, 'The Iceman Cometh: An extract from These Things Happen by Greg Fleet', '12.jpg', 'The Iceman Cometh: An extract from These Things Happen by Greg Fleet', '<div>\r\n<p>WARNING: Graphic content and coarse language</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>I AM not anti-drugs. I believe that there are things to be learned from taking certain drugs. Drugs can take you down a road to enlightenment. Drugs can be fun.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But ice? No.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ice, if it chooses to take you anywhere, will eventually try to take you backwards down a one-way alley that leads to madness, fear, irrationality, delusion, suicide and murder. Most of those don&rsquo;t fit under my subheading of &ldquo;fun&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This may be a crap analogy, but if you can consider drugs as children, ice (or crystal meth) is the bad seed. The kid that will start killing pets and then grow into a serial murderer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;That kid just ain&rsquo;t no good.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As with most children, ice is so cute and fun when it&rsquo;s still a baby. But as it grows, you start to notice things. Like how it will never meet your eyes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the reasons this drug has the ability to tear your world apart is that, like most bad relationships, the beginning is heavenly. You feel confident and capable. Strong and more focused than ever before. You feel as though you could do anything. And you probably could. This may be why the Japanese (who I&rsquo;ve been told invented the drug) gave meth to their kamikaze pilots.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Fly this plane into that ship.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;No way.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;OK, take this drug. Now fly this plane into that ship.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Cool.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I have taken ice. I have smoked it, I have injected it, I have snorted it. Believe me, I am not bragging. I am attempting to show you how, in certain situations, I know what I&rsquo;m talking about. At one point around 2004-05, my then-partner Catherine and I took ice for about six months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="This is an edited extract of Greg Fleet’s memoir These Things Happen, released by Macmill" src="http://resources1.news.com.au/images/2015/08/23/1227494/947289-3081f936-47bd-11e5-a05e-f1249120d4d6.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:1000px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>This is an edited extract of Greg Fleet&rsquo;s memoir&nbsp;These Things Happen, released by Macmillan Australia on Tuesday. RRP $34.95.&nbsp;<em>Source:&nbsp;Supplied</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For a fairly gruesome description of that time, read on, Macduff.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The reason that Catherine and I were taking ice was because I&rsquo;d recently had a naltrexone implant surgically inserted into my body, in an effort to stop taking heroin. Naltrexone is a chemical that acts on the brain&rsquo;s opioid receptors and, among other things (though this is the biggie), blocks the euphoric feeling that accompanies the use of opiates. If you are on naltrexone you will not feel the effects of heroin, thus making using it pointless. Most implants remain effective for about six months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To get a naltrexone implant you must first dry out, or go through withdrawal from heroin and stay off it for three days or so. You then go to a cold and sterile clinic where a doctor will make an incision about 10 centimetres below your navel. The doctor will scrape around inside the incision with a scalpel (the worst part) and make a hole big enough to fit the implant. A naltrexone implant is about three centimetres long and half a centimetre wide. They then insert the implant into the hole and sew you up. You can feel it as a hard lump under your skin. And for about six months you will no longer feel the effects of heroin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are as committed a heroin user as I was, you will go out and have some heroin just to see if it works or not.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But a naltrexone implant is a quick fix. It&rsquo;s like putting nail varnish on a cracked windscreen. It will work for a while, but one day that shit is going to cave in on you. Probably in about six months, and probably when you are driving.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As soon as I had my new cyborg-like upgrade, I left the clinic and scored. I took the heroin. I waited. And &hellip; nothing. I felt nothing. I was free!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I wasn&rsquo;t free. I was just out on parole.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And if heroin was a prison from which I&rsquo;d just been released, I was about to start taking a drug that was a psych ward.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A loony bin.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A ship of fools. Ice, ice, baby.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><a href="http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/special-features/australias-drug-epidemic-a-9000km-trip-through-the-heart-of-our-ice-nation/story-fnknbqfy-1227492930943" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(3, 115, 179); text-decoration: none;"><img alt="ice" src="http://resources2.news.com.au/images/2015/08/23/1227495/022062-a1031f5c-4928-11e5-a05e-f1249120d4d6.jpg" style="border:none; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:366px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>During early meth use, no problem seems insurmountable. You feel as though your brain and body are operating at an elevated level. And then there is the sex. This will be difficult because I, in no way, want people to take ice, not even once. By the end of this chapter I imagine you will know why I feel that way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But the sex &hellip;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>My sex life up until that point had been fairly pedestrian. I am, generally speaking, fairly quiet during sex. I&rsquo;m not demonstrative. I don&rsquo;t yell porn cliches. If anything, I get intimidated by people who do. I enjoyed sex, but I was more driven by the desire for heroin. And heroin makes you not really care about sex. It makes you not really care about anything.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We started doing things I had never done. We started playing roles when we had sex. We would pretend to be other people. At first, those people were types: bikers, professors, handymen and bored sex-mad cellists. It was amazing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then we started having sex with each other while pretending to be various people that we actually knew. I cannot begin to explain the complexities and thrills of that game. To this day I see people I know and think, I have sort of had sex with you, and it was brilliant, or worse, I think, I have had sex with someone while pretending to&nbsp;beyou.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For us, sex on ice was deep and wild and compelling. It lasted hours and was usually performed in front of a full-length mirror. (I was thinner then.)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This was all happening in the first three weeks or so of us taking ice. Looking back now, I can see that we were already going insane. We honestly thought we were in heaven, and perhaps we were. But we had travelled there on wings made of wax. And what is it that they say about flying too close to the sun?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ice, ice, baby.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="Greg Fleet holding in 2007." src="http://resources0.news.com.au/images/2015/08/23/1227494/947792-c338cb5e-47c9-11e5-a05e-f1249120d4d6.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:366px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>Greg Fleet holding in 2007.&nbsp;<em>Source:&nbsp;News Limited</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>About two months into our ice usage, the glory days of amazing sex and elevated thought began, almost imperceptibly, turning to shit. The maze was no longer easy to navigate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With most long-term drug use, what the user is doing is trying to get back to the beginning. Back to the early days when the drug made you feel so good. But you can never get back there. Back there does not exist anymore. Not on this timeline. It&rsquo;s a false economy. But you will keep trying. Eventually it becomes like a snake swallowing its own tail. Sad and destructive and doomed to nothingness.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;If we have just one more &hellip; just one more &hellip; I KNOW we can get back there. I&rsquo;m pretty sure I know &hellip;&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You don&rsquo;t. You can&rsquo;t. I&rsquo;ve tried.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may think that you are good with directions, or that you can remember the map. But the map is always changing. It&rsquo;s in a constant state of flux. You could get lost and wander off the edge of the world (if the world wasn&rsquo;t so round and full of oceans).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Catherine and I must have known subconsciously that this experiment was doomed to end badly. We started turning on each other. Things became not very nice. But we stayed the course. We kept running because that was all we knew how to do.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Two months into our ice use, I had to go on a comedy tour to Perth (yay!) and the regional north of Western Australia (boo!). I&rsquo;m not trying to be mean to places like Port Hedland, but when you are 4000 kilometres away from your lover and you are experiencing amphetamine psychosis for the first time, the last place you want to be is some town where the most interesting things to see are racism and sand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Flying to Western Australia meant suddenly being without ice. This was the early 2000s and the likelihood of stumbling over crystal meth in Perth was small. Ironically and dangerously, ice is now all over that fair city and, to be honest, most cities. It&rsquo;s a scourge. Up to that point, I thought heroin was the only drug that was hard to come off. I was clearly very wrong. While ice, for me at least, was not so much physically hard to withdraw from, it was emotionally and psychologically devastating. I went into psychosis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And, like most insane people, I had no idea that I was insane. The psychosis that I experienced by suddenly stopping ice was revealing itself as extreme fear and rampant paranoia. I began to catastrophise. For the two weeks I was on tour, I became convinced that on the other side of the country, Catherine was not only taking ice and having fun but that she was f***ing other people and having orgies. It was not the idea of her having random sex with several people at once that upset me. If I had been there in that situation, I would have jumped in with both feet.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What terrified me, being 4000 kilometres away from her in some desert town, was that I had been forgotten. That life, our life, was going on without me.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I had heard of the term &ldquo;the tyranny of distance&rdquo;, but I had never felt it before, and it felt like my funeral.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It felt like I was dead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I became irrationally obsessed with the idea that Catherine had abandoned me. I called or sent long, accusatorial text messages about 30 times a day. For 15 days. That&rsquo;s about 450 times, or what the Dutch would call &ldquo;a shitload of phone calls&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Catherine said and did nothing to alleviate my fears. Because she, too, was, by that stage, quite mental; I think she rather enjoyed all the drama. She let my mania run wild.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She certainly had my full attention.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now, keep in mind that while all of this madness was going on, I was travelling around with six other people doing stand-up comedy every night.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I was the craziest person on planet Earth, and my job was to make people happy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Having been a drug addict for close to 20 years by that stage, I was used to performing in various stages of disrepair. That comes with the territory of:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Being a comedian,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Being a drug addict and, more importantly,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Being both.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While I had clearly, at times, been trashed on stage, I rarely worked completely shitfaced. I have always known that having the ability to control a room makes for better gigs. While I didn&rsquo;t often work smashed, I worked even less often completely sober. As important as control is, I also always felt that getting a little bit loose was usually helpful to create a vibe of relaxation and thrills at the same time. What I did even less often than working smashed or sober was work while going through withdrawal. That combination of desperation, fear and hunger for chemicals, mixed with the physical pain of detoxing, makes it hard to concentrate on entertaining a room full of strangers. Occasionally I had worked while going through heroin withdrawal and it was horrible, but nothing like this. I was unravelling daily. I was having a mental breakdown, but I didn&rsquo;t know it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>During the shows, I could for the most part fake it. Say things that I knew were funny because I&rsquo;d said them before and people had laughed. Sometimes, while in the middle of a routine, I would catch myself thinking about Catherine and how unfair everything was. It was unlike how I would normally work, but it was all that I had. For the most part, I got away with it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But a few times, someone in the crowd would do or say something negative, yell something out. This is part of my job. Even though I don&rsquo;t like it, I deal with it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But back then? Four thousand kilometres away? In that state of mind? I lost my shit each and every time it happened. It did only happen a few times, but that was a few times too many.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It usually went down like this. Some arsehole would yell out some fairly innocuous comment and I would say something cutting to put them in their place. The rest of the audience would laugh and clap. So far, so normal. Comedy 101.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But then, I wouldn&rsquo;t let it go. I would continue to berate the person with vicious and deeply personal attacks. I was like a fighter who didn&rsquo;t stop when his opponent was unconscious. Relentless abuse. And it would come in waves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;You tiny little man, you piece of f***ing shit &hellip; Have you got anything else to say? No? Of course not. You are a coward. You are scum. I can smell the creepy loneliness just oozing out of your pores. You are the worst part of all of our lives. Seriously man, kill yourself. You know that you should. Go home and eat a f***ing gun, you waste of oxygen. You vacuum. You nothingness.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And as I said these things, I meant every word.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="Ice didn’t make Greg Fleet a nice person." src="http://resources0.news.com.au/images/2015/08/23/1227494/947820-1ae21a06-47c8-11e5-a05e-f1249120d4d6.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:366px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>Ice didn&rsquo;t make Greg Fleet a nice person.&nbsp;<em>Source:&nbsp;News Limited</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This was beyond the call of duty. Not even an attempt at banter or being clever. Just flat-out, horror-show abuse. Language as a weapon. Inevitably, when I would finally stop (and this would sometimes go on for five minutes or more), I would sense that something fundamental had changed. I would look out at the rest of the audience, the very same people who had clapped and giggled at my early put-down of the interloper, and they would be looking back at me in abject fear.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I didn&rsquo;t know if the fury came from the drugs, the lack of drugs, or if it had always been in me, down in the darkest place, lying dormant. Wherever it came from, whatever had spawned it, it was out in the light now, and it was a monster. It was as though I was murdering someone. And on some level I was, just not the person that they thought I was murdering.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On my return from the wild west, things returned to normal for Catherine and me, and by normal, I mean we merrily continued our descent into the third circle of hell.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As it turned out, she had indeed indulged in a little bit of extramarital fun. This caused two main problems. The obvious one was that she had had sex with someone else while I was away. That&rsquo;s a red card in most relationships. But the more insidious problem was that her doing this justified all of my madness out west. Instead of realising how crazy I had become, I suddenly felt vindicated. Those 450 phone calls were not the act of an obsessive maniac but the tragic cries in the wilderness of a lover betrayed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, Catherine and I broke up. For 24 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In that time I went and had sex with our ice dealer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I felt so much better after the sex. I felt the playing field was level again.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cuckoo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When Catherine and I got back together the next day, I told her everything. We had now both had sex with other people. She was hurt and angry but there wasn&rsquo;t a lot that she could do about it. Other than quietly plot &hellip;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I have always said that the only reason I had sex with our dealer that day was because Catherine and I had broken up. I was a free man. I was single.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That&rsquo;s bullshit. It was straight-up revenge. And revenge is a dish best served irrationally.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By now, if Catherine and I weren&rsquo;t scoring ice, we were fighting. While we were out scoring, we were fine. We had a shared goal: finding money, then obtaining more drugs. The bulk of the money came from my telling amusing tales for cash, but we also burned through her small wage every week. As long as we could focus on, say, calling my manager, or going out to the bank &mdash; whatever it took to get money &mdash; we were fine. Problem-solving was one of our few skills.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here is a sad fact: the most fun we had together in the late stage of our disease was the 10 minutes or so that we had between getting the money and buying the drugs. That little window was packed with potential and excitement. The walk from the bank to our dealer&rsquo;s flat was one of the few times that we would actually hold hands or laugh with each other.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once we had used the drugs (by then almost always injecting them to get the maximum impact) and the rush had come and gone, we were usually ready to fight. Our fights would start a few minutes after taking the drug, usually at our dealer&rsquo;s place or on the street as we walked home. The main reason that drug users fight is because they hate themselves.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are remotely bright or talented at something, but instead of chasing that dream you are chasing a drug habit, you grow to loathe yourself and those around you. I&rsquo;m sure that most of the fights between us were just projection. It&rsquo;s hard to accept that you are ruining your life, let alone that you are complicit in ruining the life of someone you love. It&rsquo;s far easier to see your partner and think, no,&nbsp;you&nbsp;are ruining&nbsp;mylife.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We shouldn&rsquo;t have been so down on each other. Our hatred of each other was just a deep dissatisfaction with ourselves. Following that line of thought, I shouldn&rsquo;t have freaked out so much when she tried to kill me.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have you noticed that people on ice will have major public screaming matches that involve intensely personal things being revealed to the world at a very high volume? Other people don&rsquo;t do that. I very recently saw two meth heads hurrying down the street in Perth squabbling at mucho decibels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lights up on two ice addicts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Her: I didn&rsquo;t suck him off, Gary, I just f***ed him twice!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gary: Well, I hope you gave him f***ing chlamydia!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What? Was this girl a loud koala in a human suit? If so, where was her clipboard and collection bucket?</p>', 16, 'en', 1, 8, 'news', 26, 1440334123, NULL, NULL, 1),
(357, 'Three families from Byron Bay reveal the realities of making a seachange', '', 'Three families from Byron Bay reveal the realities of making a seachange', '<div>\r\n<p>HAVE you ever dreamt of throwing it all in and moving to the beach &mdash; or the mountains? Seachanges used to be the domain of retirees but now about 80 per cent of people who make the change are under 50. So what&rsquo;s the motivation?</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>For us, with two children under school age, it was about finding the kind of life we wanted for our kids before they started school. We knew it was important to us to be closer to family, very close to the beach and in a place where the sense of community is strong. Endless internet research and a few family trips to NSW coastal towns honed our search the far north coast of NSW.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So what about jobs? That&rsquo;s the rub. Finding employment in paradise isn&rsquo;t easy. The mid north coast of NSW, which includes Byron Bay and Ballina, has an unemployment rate of over 8 per cent &mdash; the fourth highest in the state. The neighbouring shire of Richmond Tweed &mdash; even including the more commercial centre at Tweed Heads &mdash; has 7.7 per cent of its population unemployed. The NSW state average is 5.9 per cent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="Byron Bay is stunning, but with an unemployment rate of 7.7 per cent, getting a job makes" src="http://resources1.news.com.au/images/2015/08/22/1227494/780761-f64a5c3a-47db-11e5-a05e-f1249120d4d6.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:366px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>Byron Bay is stunning, but with an unemployment rate of 7.7 per cent, getting a job makes it tough to live there.&nbsp;<em>Source:Supplied</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It took my husband around eight months of solid job hunting to find a professional job on the Gold Coast where he is significantly more junior than he was previously. We&rsquo;ve both accepted that an hour long commute to and from work is the compromise for being in a place we love.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But it doesn&rsquo;t always start with the job.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For Leah, who moved from inner Sydney to a rural property between Byron Bay and Tweed Heads six weeks ago, it was of a more spiritual decision.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She and her husband had vague plans to start holistic health clinic near Byron Bay so when she was contacted by an acquaintance via Instagram offering her a rental property, she didn&rsquo;t hesitate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;When I got that phone call I knew I had to say yes because I was being given what I had asked for &hellip; Nothing is random. There&rsquo;s no coincidence. It&rsquo;s all been mapped out,&rdquo; Leah said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, two weeks after that fateful phone call, she moved herself and her two school aged sons to a stunning rural property at Round Mountain, four kilometres inland from Cabarita Beach. Her husband is still in Sydney and visits when he can. She is doing some consulting work as a health coach.</p>', 16, 'en', 1, 8, 'news', 26, 1440334166, NULL, NULL, 1),
(358, 'Mara Stransky, 16, on living a teenager’s life at sea', '', 'Mara Stransky, 16, on living a teenager’s life at sea', '<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="Mara Stransky, 16, originally from Queensland, has been living at sea with her parents fo" src="http://resources2.news.com.au/images/2015/08/23/1227495/237110-1de7494c-4949-11e5-8295-722838184ac6.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:366px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>Mara Stransky, 16, originally from Queensland, has been living at sea with her parents for the last five years.&nbsp;<em><em>Source:</em>News Corp Australia</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<p>FOR 16-year-old Mara Stransky traffic lights are a fascinating concept.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>After all, when you&rsquo;ve lived most of your short life on a boat, including the last five sailing the world on a 50-foot catamaran, there&rsquo;s not much need for traffic management.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ms Stransky, who lives with her parents Andrew and Caroline aboard the multihull Fantasia II says she feels more at ease on the water than she does on land.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;I do feel really at home on the boat and out on the water, more than going into a city with so many people,&rdquo; she told news.com.au during Audi Hamilton Island Race Week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;You&rsquo;re never in one place for very long and so everything is always a novelty. If you&rsquo;re out and you see pods of dolphins or whales that&rsquo;s pretty amazing but then you come into shore and you stop at traffic lights and think &lsquo;wow, someone&rsquo;s actually coordinated all of this so that the cars don&rsquo;t crash into each other&rsquo;, I think that&rsquo;s pretty amazing as well.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="Mara keeps friends, family and fans updated on her whereabouts via Facebook." src="http://resources2.news.com.au/images/2015/08/23/1227495/235918-9a2c691a-494e-11e5-8295-722838184ac6.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:488px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>Mara keeps friends, family and fans updated on her whereabouts via Facebook.&nbsp;<em>Source:&nbsp;Supplied</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ms Stransky is one of the youngest competitors at Audi Hamilton Island Race Week and despite her years, could be one of the most experienced.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On this boat alone, the trio have sailed to Indonesia, Singapore, Malaysia, the gulf of Thailand, Borneo, New Guinea as well as much of the coast of Australia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Being on and around boats is all I&rsquo;ve ever known because when I was born my parents were sailing around the world and so I sort of came into it pretty young, about four months old, Mum flew back out to meet my Dad in the Canary Islands. My first ocean passage was the Atlantic, not that I remember any of it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;To me it&rsquo;s all I&rsquo;ve ever known so it&rsquo;s normal but people are always remarking on it and for me it&rsquo;s a little hard to understand sometimes because I don&rsquo;t see it as unusual, but I guess it is.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="Mara’s home, office and school." src="http://resources2.news.com.au/images/2015/08/23/1227495/235946-99db070a-494e-11e5-8295-722838184ac6.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:488px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>Mara&rsquo;s home, office and school.&nbsp;<em>Source:&nbsp;Supplied</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ms Stransky now completes her High School studies aboard the vessel through online distance education and says some of the friends she met during a primary school stint on land are fascinated by her lifestyle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;People ask me, &lsquo;what do you do on a boats&rsquo; and I&rsquo;m like, &lsquo;what do you do in a house?&rsquo; There&rsquo;s always something to do that needs working on or fixing or general maintenance is a large part of living on a boat particularly if you&rsquo;re racing because you tend to push things a bit harder.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Plus there&rsquo;s so many things you see in the night, the moon and the stars at sea are amazing, there&#39;s no light to disturb them, there&rsquo;s just you and the stars.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="Mara Stransky aboard their catamaran Fantasia II." src="http://resources3.news.com.au/images/2015/08/23/1227495/240019-50167118-4949-11e5-8295-722838184ac6.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:488px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>Mara Stransky aboard their catamaran Fantasia II.&nbsp;<em>Source:&nbsp;Supplied</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ms Stransky&rsquo;s mother Caroline says she blown away by how well her daughter adapted to life at sea and says Mara has been the one encouraging them to enter regattas, including eleven during their three years sailing around Asia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Andrew (Mara&rsquo;s father) and I lived on a boat for 17 years before Mara came, we were sailing around the world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;We already knew that we enjoyed it but it was just a matter of whether it was more difficult to have a child and continue doing it and we&rsquo;re just lucky that she has melded in. Now she&rsquo;s actually the one driving us to get to all the regattas, we&rsquo;d be happy to slow down a bit now.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;It surprised me because if she didn&rsquo;t enjoy it, we wouldn&rsquo;t be living this life, so there more she enjoys it, the more it makes it possible for us to live this way.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="Mara Stransky, with her mother Caroline and father Andrew Stransky." src="http://resources2.news.com.au/images/2015/08/23/1227495/237498-32d2e064-4949-11e5-8295-722838184ac6.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:488px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>Mara Stransky, with her mother Caroline and father Andrew Stransky.&nbsp;<em>Source:&nbsp;Supplied</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mrs Stransky said she never had any fears for her little girl&rsquo;s safety when she was growing up on the vessel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;She grew with the boat and people would say &lsquo;aren&rsquo;t you afraid she&rsquo;ll want to jump overboard&rsquo; and I&rsquo;d say &lsquo;why would she, she&rsquo;s seen what goes on with the big waves passing by, why would she want to jump in there?&rsquo; Her balance developed really early.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As for Mara, it looks like it will always be a sailor&rsquo;s life for this young boating enthusiast.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;The more you travel the more you realise the world is such a huge place and there&rsquo;s so many new places to explore,&rdquo; she said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;I like the way it makes me feel when we get going fast, the adrenalin. To me it&rsquo;s the ultimate freedom.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;I definitely want to be involved in boats, I can&rsquo;t really imagine life otherwise, I really love boats and sailing and I don&rsquo;t want to do anything else.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="A day at the office." src="http://resources0.news.com.au/images/2015/08/23/1227495/237216-99896198-494e-11e5-8295-722838184ac6.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:488px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>A day at the office.&nbsp;<em>Source:&nbsp;Supplied</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 16, 'en', 1, 8, 'news', 27, 1440334235, NULL, NULL, 1),
(359, 'What life inside the Playboy Mansion is like', '', 'What life inside the Playboy Mansion is like', '<div>\r\n<p>FOR more than four decades, the Playboy Mansion has loomed over Hollywood, giving credibility to the self-created legend of&nbsp;Playboy&nbsp;impresario Hugh Hefner as the ultimate octogenarian Lothario.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>An invite to one of his legendary parties would guarantee champagne, celebrity guests and a devoted harem of beautiful blonde women, known as Hefner&rsquo;s &lsquo;girlfriends&rsquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now, in a tell-all book, one of the girlfriends, Holly Madison, 35, blasts away any veneer of respectable glamour that Hefner or the mansion may have once enjoyed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Madison&rsquo;s new life is miles away from the Playboy Mansion, despite the fact that when we talk, she&rsquo;s in an LA car park not far from where she spent seven years (2001 to 2008) in Hefner&rsquo;s fantasy world.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;I&rsquo;m about to go grocery shopping,&rdquo; she says, after telling me how she&rsquo;s happily married to dance-music promoter Pasquale Rotella, 41, and is mum to their daughter Rainbow, two.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Then I&rsquo;ll spend the day running after Rainbow. You know, normal mum stuff.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yet her life reads as if it were straight from the Playboy bunny playbook: a childhood obsession with Marilyn Monroe, a D-cup boob job, a move to LA in search of stardom, and her relationship with Hefner. Yet she&rsquo;s no dumb blonde. Her memoir is a self-revelatory tale that captures a society obsessed with fame and fortune at all costs.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="Holly and Hugh Hefner back in 2009." src="http://resources2.news.com.au/images/2015/08/23/1227494/858354-577eb9f6-470f-11e5-b83a-5887e9d6a545.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:366px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>Holly and Hugh Hefner back in 2009.&nbsp;<em>Source:&nbsp;Getty Images</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Some people believe I wrote the book as revenge, but it&rsquo;s not true,&rdquo; says Madison. &ldquo;The younger generation is even more obsessed with materialism, fame and looking sexy than I was, growing up. I felt an obligation to tell the truth about fame&rsquo;s dark side. I didn&rsquo;t want [reality-TV series about the Playboy Mansion]&nbsp;The Girls Next Door&nbsp;to be my legacy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It painted a very flattering picture of Hugh Hefner&rsquo;s lifestyle, the women mere accessories. There&rsquo;s a cost of living this lifestyle because, when you&rsquo;re chasing after superficial things, life becomes meaningless, depressing and empty.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Madison was a 21-year-old college student when she was spotted by Hefner&rsquo;s doctor at a bikini contest.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He invited her to a Playboy Mansion party and, naturally, the young blonde with pneumatic breasts ended up becoming a regular.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When a spot for a &lsquo;girlfriend&rsquo; opened up the next year, in August 2001, Madison jumped at the chance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;I craved glamour, fame and excitement,&rdquo; she explains. &ldquo;I thought I&rsquo;d dip my toe into the&nbsp;Playboy&nbsp;world and see what opportunities opened up. At worst, I&rsquo;d end up with a crazy story from my wild youth. However, I stepped into a trap and didn&rsquo;t leave for seven years.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The mansion&rsquo;s glamorous veneer hid a seedy side, and Madison relived a monotonous groundhog week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Saturday was movie night; Sunday, [the] fun in the sun pool party,&rdquo; she says. &ldquo;Mondays were manly night, when he&rsquo;d have his guy friends over. Hef&rsquo;s wife [the pair had separated, and later divorced] and two sons, who lived next door, came on Tuesdays for family night. Wednesday and Friday nights, we&rsquo;d glam up and go to the hottest clubs in town.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There were also designated sex nights when, after clubbing, the girlfriends would return to Hefner&rsquo;s room, smoke pot and half-heartedly engage in group sex.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="“You played by Hef’s rules or you were out,” says Madison." src="http://resources2.news.com.au/images/2015/08/23/1227494/858542-b78aae7c-470f-11e5-b83a-5887e9d6a545.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:366px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;You played by Hef&rsquo;s rules or you were out,&rdquo; says Madison.&nbsp;<em>Source:&nbsp;Getty Images</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hefner maintained complete control over the young women&rsquo;s lives. On their nights off, they had to be back in the mansion by 9pm. &ldquo;You played by Hef&rsquo;s rules or you were out,&rdquo; Madison says. &ldquo;He had a revolving door of girls coming and going before I entered the situation. He was savvy about what kept a woman there, such as giving us a weekly $1000 clothing and beauty allowance, or paying for plastic surgery. I had my nose done on his account.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>His strategy for control included pitting the women against each other.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Before I went into the mansion, I was confident about how I looked. Then I found myself trying to compete: who was the prettiest/skinniest/bustiest/most tanned/most baby-faced, with the longest, whitest hair? I was made to feel ugly by girls I referred to as the &lsquo;mean girls&rsquo;. Like I was this homely girl, lucky to be there. I started to believe nobody else would want me.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But it was in Hefner&rsquo;s interests to have girlfriends who didn&rsquo;t get along. &ldquo;He loved the drama!&rdquo; recalls Madison. &ldquo;It gave him the sense of being fought over and desired.&rdquo;</p>', 16, 'en', 1, 8, 'news', 28, 1440334283, NULL, NULL, 1),
(360, 'The struggles of women with big breasts', '', 'The struggles of women with big breasts', '<div>\r\n<p>CAROL Whitmore hated her 38H breasts so much that she went on national television begging someone to help her fund breast reduction surgery.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;It was just embarrassing,&rdquo; Carol, who lives in Auckland, told news.com.au. &ldquo;People would stare at my boobs because they stuck out so much. You feel frumpy and matronly because boobs that big are not sexy &mdash; they&rsquo;re big and heavy and they get in the way.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;You get big dents in your shoulders from the bra straps holding the weight of your breasts. Going swimming was a nightmare,&rdquo; she said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 2002, the then 41-year-old did the morning TV show rounds and was spotted by Port Macquarie breast surgeon Guy Hingston, who has been performing breast reduction surgeries for almost 20 years.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr Hingston was living in New Zealand at the time and offered Carol a free reduction procedure. He paid for all the costs and performed the surgery in Auckland. She had 2.2kg of breast tissue removed and is now a D cup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;It&rsquo;s the best thing I&rsquo;ve ever done,&rdquo; said Carol, now 57. &ldquo;I felt like I was normal, like other women. It was so exciting waking up from the surgery and looking down and having normal sized boobs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;I could go and get nice beautiful bras and tops and swimming togs. I was over the moon.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Prior to having surgery, Dr Hingston says his patients are &ldquo;depressed, self conscious and unable to wear the clothes they want to wear.&rdquo; They range between a C and an H cup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;There&rsquo;s a huge limitation in the exercise they can do. The distraction it causes in all of their relationships &mdash; both personal and professional &mdash; it really is a significant problem,&rdquo; he said.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Women like Carol are speaking up about the battles of having big breasts, afterModern Family&nbsp;actress Ariel Winter&nbsp;<a href="http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/celebrity-life/modern-family-actress-ariel-winter-gets-a-breast-reduction/story-fn907478-1227481244256" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(3, 115, 179); text-decoration: none;" target="_blank">revealed last week that she went under the knife</a>to reduce her 14F cup to a 16D.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;As women in the industry, we are totally oversexualised and treated like objects,&rdquo; the 17-year-old told&nbsp;<a href="http://www.glamour.com/inspired/blogs/the-conversation/2015/08/ariel-winter-breast-reduction" style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgb(3, 115, 179); text-decoration: none;" target="_blank">Glamour</a>. &ldquo;Every article that has to do with me on a red carpet as to do with &lsquo;Ariel Winter&rsquo;s Crazy Cleavage!&rsquo; or &lsquo;Ariel Winter Shows Huge Boobs at an Event!&rsquo; And that&rsquo;s all people would recognise me by.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>She had the surgery on June 4 and says she can&rsquo;t wait feel more confident on the red carpet at the Emmys next month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><img alt="New Zealand woman Carol Whitmore, pictured here in 2002, after her breast reduction." src="http://resources3.news.com.au/images/2015/08/22/1227494/620667-38ea7e1a-46f3-11e5-b83a-5887e9d6a545.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; font-family:inherit; font-stretch:inherit; font-style:inherit; font-variant:inherit; font-weight:inherit; height:1000px; line-height:inherit; margin:0px; padding:0px; vertical-align:baseline; width:650px" /></div>\r\n\r\n<p>New Zealand woman Carol Whitmore, pictured here in 2002, after her breast reduction.&nbsp;<em>Source:&nbsp;Supplied</em></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>MORE WOMEN ARE GOING UNDER THE KNIFE</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Breast reductions are one of the most common plastic surgery procedures performed in Australia, according to the Australian Society of Plastic Surgeons. And it&rsquo;s one of the most rewarding for both patients and surgeons, says the society&rsquo;s spokesman Dr Jeremy Hunt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;I&rsquo;ve seen patients who wear KKK bras at the age of 22,&rdquo; said Dr Hunt, who has performed the surgery on women aged 14-70. &ldquo;They&rsquo;ve become withdrawn and can&rsquo;t interact socially.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Patients often suffer from back, neck and shoulder pain, rashes under their breasts and find it very difficult to find clothes that fit properly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;In my mind, a breast reduction is all about quality of life and unlocking patients from the border that they carry,&rdquo; he said. &ldquo;My aim is to bring people into proportion, which usually means reducing them to a manageable C-D. Socially, my patientsbecome less withdrawn, more outgoing, more confident and live fuller, happier lives.&rdquo;</p>', 16, 'en', 1, 8, 'news', 28, 1440334335, NULL, NULL, 1),
